{"/service/ndnp/ohi/batch_ohi_gatsby_ver01/data/sn83035274/00279555727/1945091301/0512.xml":{"full_text":"IS. Skplrmter 1945\nCLEV ELAND EAST\nNEWS\nby Ethel\nO., SqW IS\u2014Laut\nrriday we, had a business meetA\ntog and a few important events\nWere dhcussed. First of all, on\nNov. 24 the Cleveland East Jrs.\nare hax nig a dance and every\none i. invited to attend, that goes\nto our out-of-town clubs to. Do\nnot fc- get, Nov. 24.\nTh certainly was* some par\nty th.it Bob Z\u00fccker had. We cer\ntainly \u00ablad a riprroaiing time.\nEspecially eating \"Kukarutz\"\n(corn to those who can't read\nSaxon- it certainly hit the Spot.\n\"Hei in\" can sure plav those\nolkas\u2014keep it tip Hermann.\u2014\nince when does a certain chap\nanswc o \"Cook\u2014ie\nThanks loads Mr. and Mrs.\nZucker, vfrything was grand.\nOn !y half of the club and my\nself we *vou1d like to congratu\nlate Dot Melzkr on her engage\nment to Ensign Bill Stamp. Here\nis all the luck in the world to\nboth of ou.\nAlso we- would Md to tell Ell\nwood City that we're looking\nforward to the Victory Dance.\nYou can be sure that as many of\nus that van come will be there.\nWEDDING\nANNOUNCEMENT\nMr. and Mrs. George Letzncr\nof 3558 Lloyd Road announce the\niparriagc of their daughterLouise\n|d Elmer H. Parge, Jr. S. A. D.\n|/c, son of Mr. and Mis. E. II.\njjparge, Sr., of California. Vow\u00ab\nfrill l\u00bbe taken at Teutsch Evan\nielical Lutheran Church. West\n\u20229th and Willard Ave, on Sept.\nf5, 1945, at 6:30 P. M. Open\nlurch wilt be observed.\n'OUNGSTOWN NEWS\n\"By Lou and Min.\n^'Youngstown, O., Sept. 13\u2014We\n^Had our usual meeting last week\nSnd quite a number of members\nAttended. Nice going, but where\nwere the rest of you I*\nOur financial secretary David\nBokesch read the names of the\nIjiembcrs who are back in their\nDues. Yt'U all know who you are,\naip.Jiow about paying up. Q.K.:\nJr. Advisors\nAlong tfrith our advisor, Geo.\nKascher, we nave three newly\nfleeted ones: Mike Art?., Gus\nSchoi and Benny Scharsu.\nCorn Roast\nOur social committee for this\niponth lias planned i corn roast,\nwill be held Saturday night,\nept. 15. from 9 P. M. till??\nftPlace: Picnic Grounds in Wick\nit'flfe. Me.nbers of committee are:\nptoris Kucheruk, Jone Thorn.\nf\u00c9ermati XVagner and Bob Haner\nV Dance\nJust a reminder to keep Oct.\n|3 open tor the danc*' in Youngs\n\u00e9own.\n7 Remember our meetings are\nheld every Thursday\nI\nit\nills\nfl /inrti IV\u00bb\n7:30 p.m.\niiimi\nhii\ni rrm\nALBERT E.\nZIEHM\nl^eichenbestatter\n\u2022:jX\n(fHMMn wem)\nUk'jibutattaapLaia\n|7618 Superior Ave.\nim\nCLEVELAND WEST\nNEWS\nBy Elsie \"Flash\" Fleischer\nCleveland, S\u00e9pt. !3\u2014Last\nFriday night proved to be quite\nexciting We got a preview o\nwhat it will be like when all of\nour boy3 come home. Yoi! First\nof all we have John Weber of the\nU. S. Army who is now home on\nleave. We've been seeing him a\nround quite a bit. By the way.\nJohn, did you get that Social call\nout of the way yet\"' Next we\nhave Johnnie Hallner of the Na\nvy. He dropped in for a few days.\nI don't think anyone was hap\npier to see him than his wife\nIrene, and of course, little \"Spi\nke\". You surprised us John, w~\nhadn't expected to see you for\nquite some time yet. Last, but\nnot least the biggest surprise of\nall was when Bill Folberth walk\ned in. Bill, just returned from\nItaly, will be home until October\n8th. It is good having yau around\nagain I\u00bbi\u00abl, and you site looking\njust grand. And that takes care\nof the returned service men of\nFriday night. Now for the two\ngirls from the land of Sunshine,\nCalifornia. Mrs.Marie Mathiesen\nand Mis. Vera (call her Jan')\nStolz both got back last week\nand believe it or not, are plan\nning to stay home for a while.\nIt's good seeing you girls again\nand we hope you decide to make\nyour 'visit home a permanent\none. And that takes care of our\nhomecomings for a while.\nIn the future, play practices\nwill begin at 7:30 in the Sachsen\nheim on Wednesday evenings.\nBe prompt.\nThis Fjiday is the night of the\nBirthday Social. 7 hope the birth\nday children do not forget be\ncause we are not forgetting.\nSaturday night found East and\nWest in full swing at the Zucker\nhousehold. Because of the wea\nther we dispensed with the beach\nparty, although a few couldn't re\nsist the nice and cool, lake on\nsuch a scorching day. We had\na 'Better than Good' time. We\nhaven't been to a birthday party\nfor such a long time that we\nfigured that we had better make\nup for lost time. And we did.\nYou should have seen\nMarty op' Schuster on the Re\nducing Machine. Did it help Mar\nty? Bob 'Zuckie' Zucker cook\ning coii:ee. Never mind any of the\nremarks made by these who do\nnot know good coffee. It was\ngood. Even Kay 'Baby' Rehner\nhad some and that is going soniv\nsince she is strictly a Milk Drin\nker. __ Hilda 'Let's Polka' Anto\nnius trying her darndest to polka\nsmoothly on a hard rubber floor\nIt was not easy, was it Hil?\nAll the people who met \"Zunch\".\nWh6 is he anyway With that\nI'll leave you until\na lint'\nAre yon and yoar relatives\nben of the lick Bene\u00ab Society\nand Central Verband? If not, now\nis\nthe time to Join. For more Infor\nmation call the local representative.\nLearn Today\nEarn Tomorrow*\nIIIUNDP\u00ab HOW,.\nSPRY AS A COLT\nthanks to this\nMGHEHERff*\nTONIC\nOlder people 1 If you\nhavent the stamina you\nshould\u2014because your summer diet\nlacks the natural A ft Vitamins and\nenergy-building, natural oils you need\n\u2014you'll find good-tasting Scott's\nEmulsion rich in these Vital Elements.\nIt helps tone up the system, build\nstamina, energy and resistance. Try it I\nSee a wonderful difference\u2014buy\neconomical Scott's today\nT'Y SCOTT'S\nI\nE U S I O N\nV y AR ROUND 10 NU\nEND BURN MISERY!\nNew discovery bring* almost I\u00abstent\nrelief for minor baas, scalds, cuts,\n\u2022kin Irritations. Get\nNSW\nSCOTT'S\nOINTMENT eoMslnlar cod liver oil\nwith \u00abotwrsl A end Vitamin* to\nBoothins-heeMn* quick notion.\nllBey todew at drnssist's.\nSGT. OSCAR KOHL\nHome on Furlough\nSgjt. O. Kohl, former !*res. T.\nS. J. A., ai rived home on fur\nlough and found Mrs. Kohl and\ntheir son Buster\" waiting at the\ndepot for him. Incidentally Sgt.\nKohl and S/Sgt. Buster had not\nseen ea**h other for 26 months.\nBuster having just returned from\n18 months service in ihe S. W.\nPacific in an Combat Eng. group.\nThe furlough also including\nSgt. and Mrs. Kohl celebrating\ntheir wedding anniversary with\nmany guest being present includ\ning Mrs. Kohi's sister Mrs. .W.\nSimonis of Gary, Indr\nThe furlough had another great\nevent in a- much as Sgr. Kohl as\na boy witnessed 'Armistice day'\nin Cleveland in 1918 he had the\nprivilege of being home on Vic\ntory Day this time and helping\ncelebrate it also.\nSgt. Kohl is still w\u00abth the Mili\nvtary Police being stationed -it\npresent in Cp. Beauregard. La.,\nwhile S/Sgt. Buster is back at\nKennedy Gen'l Hospital, Mem\nphis, Tenn.. undergoing treat\nment.\nSgt. Kohl remarked about the\nspirit oi the Saxon youth espec\nially the gills in keeping the T.\nS. J. A. together, which once\nagain proves Build? Sand\nor Rock. A group built on the\nSands of Personality soon crum\nbles and vanishes. The group\nbuilding on The Bed Rock of\nPrinciple goes on forever.\nOscar :s now expecting a dis\ncharge and hopes to return homo\nsoon. He is a former member of\nCleveland West and East and i\nmember of Branch 1 in the Cen\ntral Verband for 17 years.\nO\nCHICAGO SOUTH\nSIDE JUNIORS NEWS\nBy Gertrude Salmen\nChicago. Ill, Sept. 13\u2014The\nChicago Jrs. are celebrating their\n5th anniversary on Sept. 16. We\nare goit._ down town to the show\nI and dinner. We will meet \"under\nthe clock\" at Randolph and State\nat 2 o'clock. Let's make this a\ngood old Saxon party.\nThe new members of our club\nare Michael Obert Jr. and Arthur\nSalmon. We hope that on our\nfuture anniversary we will have\nmany more new members.\n6th Edition\nICE\nCAPADES\nOF 1946\nSept. 21 thru Oct 7\nKttisNi Sun. Sept. 33-30, Ost. 7\nTHOCSANDS WHRb TVRXED\nAWAY LAST V K A K\nSEATS ON SALE NOW\nWeek Brite\u00ab: $2.90, $2.50, $1.90\nfTat. and San.: S3.60, $11.80, $3.10\nOwn. Adm.: $1.30 Week days\nS1.30 Sat. and Sum.\nARENA\nor IOID1, 413 SVCUD\nGOOD NEWS!\nTo*AH Who Need\nLaxative Now-asd-Thes\nWhen yen feel sluggish, stomech upsst\nlow in spirits end somewhat \"no account\u2122\n\u2014because you need a good denning out\u00bb\nwhat you then should try is Xruschen-*\nepeedy saline laxative\u2014which the know*\ntog Public the world ever has bought to\nthe tune of ever 245 MILLION bottle\u00ab\nto data.\nWhen you want relief you want te\niPRONTO*\u2014you don't want to wait soar\nhours (Knischen acts usually within ia\nhour)\u2014and with Kruschon there's a mini\nof Kftddw iDCOBYIfiilOl diflMDdS\nand recurrences.\nSo whenever you feet the need of\nlaxative, just LET YOURSELF IN FOR\nTHE QUICK RELIEF THAT KRU*\nSCHEN SALTS CAN BRING YOU.\nNotice how much more alert\u2014more active\nyou feel after your first experience with\n\u00abraschen Salts. There are a lot of sur\nprising things we could tell you about\nKruscnon Salts but we will let you find\nthem out for yourself.\nYew can obtain KRUSCHEN SALTS\nfrom any drug store on the maker's an*\nsurance of double your money back if nog\nactually overjoyed with the pleasing re*\nsuits. Caution use only as directed. Reg*\nelate the dose to suit your own require*\nGet KRUSCHEN SALTS today\nsehen\nis,\nALL\nSiebenb\u00fcrgisch-Amerikanisches Volksblatt\nCANTON ECHO\nBy Lillian Bremer\nCantotJvQ., Sept. 13\u2014First of\nall I thank Salem for the wonder\nful time that they showed us on\nLabor Day. It certainly was a\nhang up affair and let's hope we\ncan get vogether more oftener in\nthe near future.\nOur monthly meeting was held\nSeptember 7 and we are glad to\nwelcome a new* member, Audrev\nRoth. Here's h\u00f6ping that you'll\nbe with us for long time.\nWe wore gl\u00e2d to see Bill Untch\nand Ot'.o Bahmillcr at our meet\ning and iiope that more of ou\nmembers now in service will soon\nbe with us also. Bill has just fur\nnished his Army basic training\nand Otto is home from overseas.\nFrom now on our meetings\nwill be held on a Saturday due to\nthe convenience of many of our\nmembers.\nOur next\nedosest\nget-together\nis the dance on Oct. 6 given by\nEllwood City Jrs. and to which\nevery other Saxon club is invited.\nSo come on Canton and let's\nshow F.\n11,wood that we have the\nget up and go and let's go in\na large group. We had fun at Sa\nlem and with the kind of mem\nbers we have in our vlub I know\nwe can iiave fun in Ellwood.\nSo what do you say1\nSALEM NEWS\nBy Gertie Girscht\nSalem. O. Sept. 13\u2014Our Labor\nDay picnic turned out to be a big\nsuccess and our thanks go to ail\nwho attended. Most Jr. club\niwei*e veiy well represented ex\ncept lor Youngstown. What's\nwrong Youngstown? With bowl\ning and busket ball coming it will\ngive the Jrs. something to do. I\nam sure Ellwood City can look\nforward :o 'seeing the SH^etn\ngang at t'ieir dance Oct. 6.\nOncc ntoi e, at this: time we\nwish to (hank ou~ St Lodge\nmembers for their splendid helv\nat our picnic. Also to the Corn\nmittec who worked hard in ar\nranging it.\nService Notes\nCp'. Gordon Melow arrived\nhome on Friday night and will\nreceive a discharge soon Glad to\nhave you back Gordy.\nAlso home for 30 ('ay. is Emil\nUntch and George Wcerther.\nHope both of you er joy {your\nwell deserved furloughs.\nI hear the Chief of Police paid\nMarge Vv nius a visit last week.\nDid he make you pay that fine\nfor the false report you put\nabout a Saxon neighbor\nAn apology goes to Bill Krauss\nand Martha Binder. I 'ie two are\nnot euga.-.ed Where did the ring\ncome frvn, Martha?\nSalem Jrs. Notice\nAll Jrs. having books for the\nCedar chest are to turn them in\nby Sept. 15. The cedar chest will\nbe given \u00abway Sept. 29 at the\nclub. t'\nINDIGESTION\nmay exci